{"word":"πολύμοχθος","slug":"πολύμοχθος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πολύμοχθος</b></el> <el>(πολύ-μοχθος, ον,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>much-labouring, suffering many things</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>won by much toil</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>: <i>wrought with much toil</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}